# two mutually exclusive things, such that one can only choose one over another
#: {{uxi|fr|Tu ne peux pas avoir '''le beurre et l’argent du beurre'''.|You can't '''[[have one's cake and eat it too|have your cake and eat it too]]'''.}}

====Usage notes====
While the French expression is used mostly with {{m|fr|avoir}} and {{m|fr|vouloir}}, a variety of construction with verbs such as {{m|fr|obtenir}} or {{m|fr|garder}} are possible, unlike in English.

